name: GKError.Code
desc: Error codes for the GameKit error domain.

items.name: case gameUnrecognized
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because Game Center doesn’t recognize the app.

items.name: case notSupported
items.desc: The app doesn’t have Game Center enabled.

items.name: case unknown
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation due to an unknown error.

items.name: case cancelled
items.desc: The system canceled the requested operation or the user disabled it.

items.name: case communicationsFailure
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation due to an error communicating with the server.

items.name: case invalidPlayer
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the player is invalid.

items.name: case invalidParameter
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because one or more parameters are invalid.

items.name: case gameSessionRequestInvalid
items.desc: The properties of the game session request are impossible to fulfill.

items.name: case apiNotAvailable
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the API isn’t available.

items.name: case connectionTimeout
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the connection timed out.

items.name: case apiObsolete
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because Apple deprecated the API.

items.name: case userDenied
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the user denied it.

items.name: case invalidCredentials
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the user name or password are incorrect.

items.name: case notAuthenticated
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the system hasn’t authorized the player.

items.name: case authenticationInProgress
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the local player is already authenticating.

items.name: case parentalControlsBlocked
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the user disabled this feature in Restrictions.

items.name: case playerStatusExceedsMaximumLength
items.desc: The player’s status exceeds the maximum length.

items.name: case playerStatusInvalid
items.desc: The player’s status is invalid.

items.name: case underage
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because this feature isn’t available to underage players.

items.name: case playerPhotoFailure
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation to retrieve a player’s photo.

items.name: case ubiquityContainerUnavailable
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the user hasn’t signed in to iCloud or hasn’t enabled iCloud Drive.

items.name: case notAuthorized
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the system hasn’t authorized the player.

items.name: case friendListDescriptionMissing
items.desc: Access to the local player’s list of friends denied for lack of a reason.

items.name: case friendListRestricted
items.desc: Access to the local player’s list of friends restricted.

items.name: case friendListDenied
items.desc: Access to the local player’s list of friends denied.

items.name: case friendRequestNotAvailable
items.desc: The player can’t send a friend request at this time from this device.

items.name: case matchRequestInvalid
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the match request is invalid.

items.name: case unexpectedConnection
items.desc: An unexpected player has connected to a match.

items.name: case invitationsDisabled
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the receiving player has disabled invitations.

items.name: case matchNotConnected
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the match isn’t connected to other players.

items.name: case restrictedToAutomatch
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the player is using automatch.

items.name: case turnBasedMatchDataTooLarge
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the match data is too large.

items.name: case turnBasedTooManySessions
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because it exceeds the maximum number of sessions.

items.name: case turnBasedInvalidParticipant
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the specified participant is invalid.

items.name: case turnBasedInvalidTurn
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the participant doesn’t have the required turn state.

items.name: case turnBasedInvalidState
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the session is in an invalid state.

items.name: case scoreNotSet
items.desc: The system can’t complete the requested operation because the system hasn’t set the score.

items.name: case challengeInvalid
items.desc: The challenge request failed due to invalid challenge data.
